Description: Multi-network peer to peer client
DescDetail: <<
 MLdonkey (mlnet) is a generic peer-to-peer file-sharing client that can
access the eDonkey2000, Overnet, Gnutella, BitTorrent, Soulseek and
Fasttrack (Kazaa) networks. Gnutella2, Direct-Connect and Open-Napster
networks also have alpha support.
<<
DescUsage: <<
 To start mldonkey either;
1. Create a directory and 'cd' to it and run the command 'mldonkey'. Note
that every time you run mldonkey after that it must from that directory.
 or
2. To start mldonkey use the command 'donkey start', to run mldonkey as a
daemon use the command 'donkey daemon' and to stop mldonkey use the command
'donkey stop'. Note if you run mldonkey this way all of the configuration
files can be found in the directory '.mldonkey' in your home directory.

 MLdonkey can be controlled via telnet (telnet 127.0.0.1 4000) and WEB
(http://127.0.0.1:4080/) interfaces. It can also be controlled using
various external GUI interfaces (mlgui).
<<
